			<description><![CDATA[<p><strong class="orangebold">Scope and Responsibilities</strong><br /> The Product Marketing Manager will play a high profile role in introducing a new, transformational technology to the marketplace, doing “whatever it takes” to ensure that Virtual Computer wins in a highly competitive enterprise software segment. For this critical role, we are seeking a competitive and self-motivated individual who combines a high level of business and technical acumen with the creativity and work ethic to outrun and outmaneuver larger and more established rivals.</p>
<p>Primary responsibilities for the Product Marketing Manager include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create marketing documents and presentations that present complex concepts in a compelling way.</li>
<li>Support the sales and executive teams with product demos and technical “air cover” in high profile customer and partnership meetings.</li>
<li>Identify, assess, and develop strategic technology partnerships in concert with product management and business development.</li>
<li>Represent Virtual Computer at trade shows and technical speaking engagements.</li>
<li>Conceptualize and produce polished and timely videos to support product marketing and blogging efforts.</li>
<li>Develop and maintain competitive analysis materials.</li>
<li>Develop and maintain detailed ROI/TCO tools, providing consultation to customers as needed.</li>
<li>Provide substantive content contributions across web and social media properties, including corporate blog, social media, and online user forums.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong class="orangebold">Desired Skills and Experience</strong><br /> Characteristics of an ideal Product Marketing Manager include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Above all else, an entrepreneurial spirit and unrelenting drive to win.</li>
<li>Bachelor’s degree in engineering, computer science, or business.  MBA is highly desirable.</li>
<li>4+ years of enterprise software experience, reflecting a mix of technical and sales/business accomplishments.</li>
<li>Deep experience with Microsoft operating systems, applications, and system management tools.</li>
<li>Conversant in the pros and cons of the latest virtualization technologies from vendors such as Citrix, VMware, and Microsoft.</li>
<li>Strategic thinker who is also willing to roll up his/her sleeves on a wide range of tasks in dynamic startup environment.</li>
<li>Outstanding writing and public speaking skills.</li>
<li>Experience with partner management and negotiation techniques.</li>
<li>Highly adept at using the latest social media tools.</li>
</ul>]]></description>
